Having only a QR code for parents to order from is very discriminatory and limiting for many of our parents. Also, not being able to manually set a due date on teacher specific URLs is stressful for me as a teacher and I know will cause panic for some of my more anxious parents. YOU might have multiple fliers out but we don't always send every flier out because of the school calendar or other issues.     I really hate all the changes this year. From the lack of $1 books which cuts off our more vulnerable students to the ways orders have cut whole populations out. Even if those ways of ordering are still available to me as a teacher, you have put MORE work on me to get that information out there. I cannot stress enough how in your effort to streamline things for teachers you've just added more stress to everything.     I'm probably reactionary messaging but this whole thing just makes me so angry that your solution was to TAKE AWAY customization!

This is my 23rd year teaching, and I'm pretty close to being done with Scholastic. I have always sent home flyers on the first Friday of the month, with orders due the following Friday. On the due date, I submit my orders, and with the exception of the COVID year, the box arrived to school within a week or two. I checked my account today because I hadn't received any notifications from Scholastic that parents had ordered, and wanted to see if that was truly the case.    I was able to see that 1 parent has ordered, but that order doesn't show up on my "pending" orders. After chatting online with a representative, I'm even more frustrated (not her fault).    Please stop the practice of auto-submitting parent online orders. This is a nightmare for teachers. The very last thing we need is to have Scholastic boxes arriving throughout each month. The rep I chatted with said that this feature cannot be turned off, and that teachers don't have the ability to change the online due date assigned

I ordered over $200 of books for my students since their parents couldn’t use the QR code and ended up paying over $27 in taxes from my own pocket! That is unacceptable!!!!! I’ve never personally had to pay taxes on my student orders and I’m very upset over these charges. All the teachers on my campus are unhappy because they too had to pay taxes for their students. Not to mention the extra amount of time that will go into distributing the books since there is no way to attach student names to the items.
